      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RIPPLES NZ (6) made a successful hit-and-run raid to NZ when overcoming a back row draw to score at Cambridge last start. That continued a string of wins and placings including a second in the Gold Bracelet from this barrier two back at Bathurst. Hasn't missed the top-three at this circuit and distance. Big chance. WILLOWS GIRL (5) is three from three this time in. Had this draw when beating Ripples in the Gold Bracelet two back and worked but was too good for the boys at Bendigo since. Could add to the winning streak. PERFECTDELIGHT (8) has been performing well without the best of luck this time in. Pushed the good filly Sparkling Sea when beaten a nose in the Golden Easter Egg last start. Draws wider but she is going well. ALWAYSBJOY NZ (10) faces a class test and wide draw won't help but she has been powering through her grades in Brisbane, winning her last four at Albion Park. STRIPES (3) is another progressing well in Queensland. Draws better than her stablemate so can be competitive.",
